  "name": "Mark 12:28–44",
  "localizedName": "Mark 12:28–44",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "One teacher of the law understood that loving God and serving others was important. These things were more important than all the other rules and practices that Jews followed. Jesus was pleased to see the man’s "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108325",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "wisdom"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Then Jesus asked questions of his own as he taught. He explained what was wrong with Israel’s teachers. They cared about their own glory and being honoured. They didn’t show concern for God’s people. Some of their rules made life harder for people like the widow giving her offering."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus pointed out that rich people were only giving God part of what they had. The widow was an example of those who "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108256",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "sacrifice"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " everything they have for God. Jesus honoured her gift."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
